We didn’t bet it, but it turns out our best pick of the first half was Juan Soto (+600), winning Barnum and Bailey’s Home Run Derby. You’re welcome. Ain’t nothin’ shakin’ but the leaves on the trees on Wednesday so we interrogated horse racing wizard Vic Cangialosi who told us there is a jumper race at Saratoga. After surveying the field, Pistol Whipped will either win or be found guilty and set free (no bail) by morning. Joe from The Bronx: “Hey Stitch, was that your van that got swallowed by the sinkhole?” Not mine, Joe. My first thought was that it had to be a CNN News van or Bill de Blasio’s. So much for home-field advantage. The Dodgers Tony Gonsolin served up a pair of homers to Giancarlo Stanton and Byron Buxton and the American League edged the National League 3-2. Loss takes us to +1,876 rayfosses.